race.comment: DAWN EMBERS (4) has run very well in two runs for the new yard, finishing runner-up two back before leading throughout to score a long overdue maiden win last time. Far too quick and off the low draw can take catching again. GOT THIS (8) was also a long-overdue maiden winner last time. The filly led throughout to score at Townsville and looks more than talented enough to take beating again. LUCKY NEKO (3) resumes and has her first run for a new yard. Trip suits fresh and can measure up in this company. HURRICANE HARLOW (1) makes debut for new yard and has placed fresh. One of the better hopes on best figures.
